<item>
            <title>[FELIX-2520] Bind method selection must not expect the component&apos;s bundle to import the service interface type</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-2520</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Our Declarative Services implementation tries to load the type of the bound service through the class loader of the component. This has the side-effect of expecting the component&apos;s bundle to actually import (and wire to) the package providing the interface.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On the other hand the Declarative Services specification states, that a bind/unbind method is acceptable if &quot;the type of the argument is assignable from the type specified by the reference&apos;s interface attribute&quot; (OSGi Compendium R4.2, Section 112.3.1, Accessing Services). This does not imply that the component must know the service type but a supertype of the service type.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For example the CT contains a test where the component&apos;s bind method expects an Object type parameter (which is certainly assignable from any type) but the component&apos;s bundle does not import the actual interface type. Thus with the current implementation the CT test fails.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
